gobuster - Gobuster is a powerful reconnaissance tool used to brute-force directories, files, and subdomains that may be hidden on a web server.


example use | gobuster dir -w wordlist.txt -u website.com

Common options
  -w wordlist.txt
  -u website.com/
  -x php,txt,html
  -o output.txt
  
  
  -q     | quite mode
  -k     | skips SSL certificate verification
  -b 404 | excludes specific HTTP status codes
  -t 50  | sets the number of concurrent threads

Modes options
  dir – Directory and file enumeration
  dns – Subdomain discovery
  vhost – Virtual host discovery
  fuzz – URL and parameter fuzzing
  s3 – Amazon S3 bucket enumeration
  gcs – Google Cloud Storage bucket enumeration

Examples
  gobuster dir -u http://example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster dns -d example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster vhost -u http://example.com -w wordlist.txt
  gobuster fuzz -u http://example.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt
